---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const siteName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_NAME ?? "PricingNest";
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`API Cost Estimation (Cost per Call) | ${siteName}`}
  description="How to estimate API cost per request, include vendor costs, and sanity-check unit economics before setting tiers."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>API cost estimation</h1>
    <p>Estimate cost per call with a simple breakdown: infra + vendor/API pass-through + fixed overhead.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card col8">
      <h2>Step 1: estimate cost per 1,000 calls</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Infra</strong>: compute, DB, queue, caches, logging/monitoring.</li>
        <li><strong>Vendor</strong>: third-party APIs, LLM calls, enrichment, email/SMS, etc.</li>
        <li>Use a blended average across regions and instance types.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Step 2: add fixed overhead</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Support, tooling, baseline infra, on-call rotation.</li>
        <li>Model fixed overhead per customer segment if you have self-serve vs enterprise.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Step 3: sanity-check for pricing</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Compare p50 vs p90 usage to avoid subsidizing heavy customers.</li>
        <li>Prefer a minimum/platform fee when overhead is meaningful.</li>
        <li>Publish examples to reduce bill shock and support load.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Tools to use</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/api-cost-estimator/">API cost estimator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/api-pricing-calculator/">API pricing calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/tiered-usage-pricing-calculator/">Tiered usage pricing calculator</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Related</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/guides/api-pricing-model/">API pricing model</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/usage-based-pricing-examples/">Usage pricing examples</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/gross-margin/">Glossary: gross margin</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

